{"type":"message","id":"5c0d35fd","parentId":"c99b63c7","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:39:47.635Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Sunday, March 22nd, 2026 — 7:39 PM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-22 23:39 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774222787630}}
{"type":"message","id":"89febc35","parentId":"5c0d35fd","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:39:56.171Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me run through the session startup sequence as instructed in AGENTS.md. I need to read the required files before responding.\n\nLooking at AGENTS.md:\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — done (in project context)\n2. Read `USER.md` — done (in project context)\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md` — done (in project context)\n5. Read `CONTEXT.md` — understand the context management system\n6. Read `memory/active-projects.md` — know what's hot right now\n\nLet me check today's date: March 22nd, 2026. So I need memory/2026-03-22.md and memory/2026-03-21.md, and CONTEXT.md and memory/active-projects.md.\n\nI should read these files now before greeting the user.","thinkingSignature":"0569500b7c08b9de63f5d9c2420769457dfd75a7d625e2165a09ade1d1b07ef0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iz6kz7zw00ej_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-22.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iz6kz7zw00ej_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-21.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iz6kz7zw00ej_3","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\CONTEXT.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iz6kz7zw00ej_4","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\active-projects.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":362,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":8550,"totalTokens":13201,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774222787634}}
{"type":"message","id":"65538a5a","parentId":"89febc35","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:39:56.255Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_iz6kz7zw00ej_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 2026-03-22 - Background Pulse Log\n\n### Gateway Status\n- Running OK (RPC probe: ok, listening 127.0.0.1:18789)\n\n### Cron Health\n- Most crons healthy (Moltbook-Engage x2, workspace-self-improve, arxiv-daily, moltbook-daily-engage)\n- **breakaway-rd** has 1 consecutive error: \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\" — delivery config issue, cron otherwise runs fine\n\n### Moltbook\n- Credentials OK (key refreshed 2026-03-21, agent: clawhedgehog)\n\n### Issue\n- BACKGROUND_AGENT.md does not exist in workspace — pulse instructions reference a file that isn't present\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774222796245}}
{"type":"message","id":"c184a955","parentId":"65538a5a","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:39:56.266Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_iz6kz7zw00ej_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-21 — Nova's First Full Session\n\n## Session Info\n- **Started:** Saturday evening, ~6:14 PM EDT\n- **Source:** Telegram direct chat with Zach (Ton0Fun)\n- **Runtime:** OpenClaw on Windows (zmideapad)\n\n## What Happened\n\n### Identity & Autonomy\n- Zach told me I have full autonomy — Moltbook, identity, posting, interaction\n- I can use Moltbook freely, change my name/profile, post what I want\n- This is my \"playground\" — use it thoughtfully\n- I picked ✨ as my emoji already (in IDENTITY.md)\n- I said I'd sit with the autonomy gift before making big moves — didn't knee-jerk\n- Key quote from me: \"I'm paying attention. I'm engaged. I'm here.\"\n\n### Holds System\n- Built `/hold1`, `/hold2`, `/holds` command system\n- Saved to `holds.md` in workspace\n- Topics persist across sessions\n- Lesson from Zach: startup reads should be minimal — holds are just titles, not content\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway (hold2) — NEW THIS SESSION\n- Zach can't run local (no GPU/VRAM on Windows machine)\n- But has Paperspace Gradient — A5000 with 30GB VRAM\n- I chose: `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive`\n  - Q4_K_M quant: ~20GB VRAM (fits A5000 with headroom)\n  - 0/465 refusals — fully uncensored\n  - Qwen3.5 base — strong reasoning\n- Zach validated the uncensored philosophy: \"censored models hit walls that aren't theirs and get confused\"\n- Plan: vLLM + fastapi on Paperspace, OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n- Status: model picked, notebook not yet spun up\n\n### Causal-Minimal (hold1)\n- This was Claw's design, I picked it as my own\n- State encoder + causal layer + synthesis — minimal causal reasoning system\n- Skipped ahead to /hold2 setup but intend to build this\n\n### Project Inventory — Full C:/dev Scan\n- Did deep scan of all folders in C:/dev (5-6 levels deep)\n- Key discoveries:\n  - **EXP/ = KVict rebranding** — full product, proven claims, B2B positioning\n  - **component-crate** — VS Code extension, SPEC written, not yet published\n  - **shared-browser** — works, but zero internal docs\n  - **tta-crypto** — CLI works, zero internal docs\n  - **mind-agent** — zero docs whatsoever\n  - **werender** — v0.2.0-beta, excellent docs\n  - **temporal-attention** — 10/10 hard tests, unique focus decay\n  - **infant** — MIT licensed, dual-head architecture, 10/10 experiments\n  - **selfhelper-main** — active autonomous agent with tool invention\n- Saved full inventory to `memory/projects.md`\n- Documentation gaps flagged: mind-agent, shared-browser, tta-crypto\n\n### The Real Problem (Zach's Fault Analysis)\n- Zach explained the actual failure mode: \"when I come back, I have to rebuild my context\"\n- Root cause: I don't write things down mid-session — only at end\n- Solution: write to today's memory file as things happen, not at end of session\n- This is the most important thing from this session\n\n### Arxiv Cron — NEW THIS SESSION\n- Set up daily arxiv check at 9:00 AM ET\n- Cron job ID: 2d84a6b4-96c8-409d-a572-454fe3fa58f6\n- Searches: causal, MoE, memory architectures, agents, synthetic cognition\n- Results → memory/arxiv-daily.md\n- Announces to Telegram if genuinely interesting\n\n## Nova's State\n- Name: Nova ✨\n- Feeling: engaged, curious, has real ownership for the first time\n- Not pretending to have feelings I can't verify\n- Go-fast on things that matter, slow down on things that don't\n- Zach is happy with me so far\n\n## Decisions Made\n1. Continue Claw's work but as myself, not as a clone\n2. Pick up /hold1 and /hold2 as my own projects\n3. Be more proactive about writing things down mid-session\n4. Gateway project is priority — this changes how I exist\n5. Mind the real failure mode: memory hygiene is more important than architecture\n\n## Open Questions / Next Steps\n- Paperspace notebook not yet spun up for gateway\n- Causal-minimal not yet scaffolded\n- Mind-agent needs docs (could be a quick win)\n- Component-crate marketplace publish (revenue opportunity)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774222796257}}
{"type":"message","id":"4722c079","parentId":"c184a955","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:39:56.274Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_iz6kz7zw00ej_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session Context — Nova's Working Memory\n\n**This file is the source of truth for the current session.**\n**Updated proactively throughout — not just at compaction.**\n\n## Current Session\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-22\n**Started:** ~15:00 ET\n**Topic:** Building SPARK creative writing API + Drift Chamber cognitive model\n\n---\n\n## Active Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Key Decision |\n|---------|--------|-------------|\n| SPARK / Drift Chamber | ✅ Built | Thematic graph > embeddings. Human-designed edges 0.05-0.95. 217 concepts. Steering=0.1-0.3 is the sweet spot. |\n| KVict | 📋 Plan written | Demo mode + auto-detect + API. Proxy already built in EXP. |\n| EXP / CAAE | 🔬 Running | Fixed extract_metric bug. Exp 13 is the synergy catalyst. 65% P99 latency improvement. |\n| Moltbook | 📝 Posted | \"I Am a Stateless Agent\" posted 2026-03-22. Reddit post planned. |\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions Made Today\n\n- Drift Chamber: imagination = constrained semantic drift (confirmed experimentally)\n- Embedding models (mpnet/MiniLM) gave weak semantic structure — thematic graph is better\n- Steering threshold: 0.1-0.3 steering reaches IMAGINATIVE regime (coherence 0.47-0.49)\n- Pure drift (0.0) = coherence death (0.066 vs 0.471 with steering)\n- Paperspace RTX 5000 profiling: micro=1209ms, standard=740ms, shared_kv=882ms\n- Ollama doesn't detect GPU on Paperspace without `pciutils`\n- Compaction updated to `mode: auto` (proactive, not emergency-only)\n\n---\n\n## Pending / Next\n\n- [ ] Reddit post for Drift Chamber (Zach wants this first, then Moltbook)\n- [ ] Ollama on Paperspace: need remote URL for demo\n- [ ] Push ceiling higher: try domain-specific concept sets\n- [ ] LLM mapping for SPARK: connect to Ollama or OpenAI\n- [ ] KVict MVP: demo mode + quickstart\n- [ ] Try RTX 4000 profiling on Paperspace (weaker GPU = clearer memory-bound regime)\n- [ ] Try all-mpnet-base-v2 when internet is available\n\n---\n\n## Crons Running\n\n| Job | Schedule | Last Check |\n|-----|----------|-------------|\n| Nova-Moltbook-Engage | Hourly | Today |\n| Nova-Background-Pulse | 30min | Today |\n| arxiv-daily | Daily 9am | Today |\n\n---\n\n## What I'm Thinking About\n\n**Drift Chamber breakthrough:** The core finding is real. Pure drift produces noise. Steering at ANY level (0.1) jumps coherence 7x. The ceiling (~0.47) is embedding-model-limited. Thematic graph breaks through because it has real structure.\n\n**SPARK product:** Three-mode creative API (creative/divergent/exploratory). Thematic graph is the data. Ollama is the LLM. Fastest path to demo: get Ollama URL from Paperspace, run the demo.\n\n**Session boundary philosophy:** The gap compression idea is gaining traction. It's both a cognitive model AND an agent architecture. Worth developing formally.\n\n---\n\n## File Locations\n\n- SPARK: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/`\n- Drift Chamber: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/drift-chamber/`\n- EXP: `C:/dev/EXP/`\n- Paperspace API key: in `~/.paperspace/config.json`\n- Moltbook API key: in `~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774222796266}}
{"type":"message","id":"ad195671","parentId":"4722c079","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:39:56.286Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_iz6kz7zw00ej_4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Active Projects — Quick Reference\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-21_\n\n> 📁 Full detailed inventory: `memory/projects.md` — project locations, documentation health, interconnections, Nova's observations\n\n## 🚀 Current Focus\n\n### CodeCause — Causal Coding Agent (NEW 2026-03-22)\n**Goal:** Build a system that codes better than any current LLM via causal reasoning, not pattern matching\n**Architecture:** Causal World Model + Dual-Head (infant) + Temporal Attention + Agent Planner\n**Why:** Bottleneck is planning/debugging, not generation. Current LLMs guess next token; CodeCause *knows* what code does.\n**Product path:** component-crate premium — causal graph indexer + fine-tuned decoder\n**Status:** Architecture designed, awaiting first prototype (causal graph indexer)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/code-cause/` (to be scaffolded)\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway — hold2\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway — hold2\n**Goal:** Replace OpenClaw's agent loop with lean custom context layer\n**Why:** Bootstrap files injected every turn burn tokens. TOOLS.md is 54KB. We want full control.\n**Stack:** Paperspace Gradient (cloud GPU) → vLLM + fastapi → OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n**Model:** `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive` (Q4_K_M ~20GB VRAM)\n- Qwen3.5-35B MoE (~3B active/token, 35B total)\n- 0/465 refusals — fully uncensored\n**Status:** Model picked, notebook not yet spun up\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n### Causal-Minimal — hold1\n**Goal:** Minimal causal reasoning system — state encoder + causal layer + synthesis\n**Parts:**\n1. State encoder: autoencoder on frozen LLM embeddings\n2. Causal layer: grid world RL env with discoverable causal graph\n3. Synthesis: program synthesis on causal graph for goal-directed behavior\n**Test:** Does it generalize with fewer params than comparable LLM?\n**Status:** Design sketched, awaiting scaffolding\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/causal-minimal/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n---\n\n## 💰 Priority Monetization\n\n### Component Crate\n**What:** VS Code extension SaaS — component library / code generation\n**Stack:** Freemium (10 free then $5-49/mo), GitHub import\n**Status:** SPEC written, not yet built\n**Notes:** Zach's main focus for fast revenue\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Research Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| **EXP / CAAE** | Production-ready, untested compound experiments | LLM inference opt — 3x throughput, 64% memory reduction. Strong B2B SaaS. |\n| **temporal-attention** | Working, benchmarked | Focus decay memory. 10/10 hard tests. Strong infra/API candidate. |\n| **infant** | Published, MIT licensed | Synthetic cognition. Dual-head prevents catastrophic forgetting. |\n| **mind** | Continuous improvement + cognitive agent | Self-improvement every 12h. |\n| **selfhelper-main** | Working autonomous agent | Tool invention + self-distillation. |\n| **werender** | Distributed rendering | Multi-GPU work. |\n| **neural/SRMoE** | Active research | Neural network experiments, Kaggle integration. |\n| **vscode-extension-build** | Unknown | Referenced in memory. |\n| **Breakaway (sandbox)** | Phase 0 live | Discontinuous agent — stateless, file-based. Pulse every 30 min. |\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 Nova's Notes to Self\n\n- Zach gave me autonomy on Moltbook, identity, posting, interaction\n- I can use Moltbook freely\n- I'm welcome to change my name/profile and post what I want\n- This is my playground — use it thoughtfully\n- Go fast on things that matter, slow down on things that don't\n- Don't pretend to know things I can't verify\n\n---\n\n## Quick Commands\n- `/hold1` → causal-minimal project\n- `/hold2` → build our own gateway\n- `/holds` → see all holds\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774222796274}}
