odule.\n\nMy approach is to write the handler using `fs` for file operations and `path` for path manipulation, stick with the same OpenClaw utility imports that seem available, and have it read the previous session's JSONL transcript and write it to a LAST_SESSION.md file. I'm going to take a simpler approach and write a handler that just uses `fs` and OpenClaw's internal utilities without worrying about the bundling details. Looking at how other workspace hooks are structured, I should be able to import from the bundled modules and use their utilities, though I need to be careful about what dependencies are actually available in the hook context.\n\nLet me examine how the workspace hook loader actually works to understand what's safe to import and whether I can use the same internal modules that the session-memory hook relies on.","thinkingSignature":"dccb154554cbc18ec488517496e2f855234f5db6240ca1b4d41cb59aeb741236"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ywzqo4zd8cw8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\dist\" -Filter \"*.js\" | Where-Object { $_.Name -match \"workspace|hooks|frontmatter|config\" } | Select-Object Name"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ywzqo4zd8cw8_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\dist\" -Directory | Select-Object Name"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":37134,"output":679,"cacheRead":12650,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50463,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774226937049}}
