{"type":"message","id":"0a710f38","parentId":"b2ef7e0d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:30:40.981Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lo16178222cn_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nThematic Concept Graph — built from thematic/structural knowledge.\nHigh quality creative data source, no internet required.\n\nUses human-designed concept relationships instead of statistical embeddings.\nBased on how humans actually understand creative concepts.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# THEME LABELS\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nCONCEPT_CLUSTERS = {\n    \"creative\": [\n        \"creativity\", \"imagination\", \"novelty\", \"innovation\", \"invention\",\n        \"originality\", \"divergence\", \"synthesis\", \"transformation\", \"recombination\",\n        \"insight\", \"intuition\", \"eureka\", \"spark\", \"emergence\",\n        \"expression\", \"artistry\", \"craft\", \"vision\", \"voice\",\n    ],\n    \"emotions\": [\n        \"longing\", \"nostalgia\", \"melancholy\", \"joy\", \"ecstasy\", \"grief\",\n        \"wonder\", \"awe\", \"dread\", \"terror\", \"hope\", \"despair\",\n        \"love\", \"passion\", \"lust\", \"yearning\", \"loss\", \"absence\",\n        \"isolation\", \"connection\", \"belonging\", \"alienation\",\n        \"ambition\", \"greed\", \"sacrifice\", \"redemption\", \"betrayal\",\n        \"courage\", \"fear\", \"resilience\", \"surrender\", \"devotion\",\n        \"memory\", \"forgetting\", \"remembrance\", \"amnesia\", \"trauma\",\n        \"identity\", \"self\", \"other\", \"mirror\", \"shadow\", \"mask\",\n        \"guilt\", \"shame\", \"pride\", \"humiliation\", \"envy\", \"compassion\",\n    ],\n    \"narrative\": [\n        \"journey\", \"quest\", \"transformation\", \"rebirth\", \"death\", \"resurrection\",\n        \"descent\", \"ascent\", \"fall\", \"rise\", \"collapse\", \"building\",\n        \"discovery\", \"secret\", \"revelation\", \"truth\", \"lie\", \"deception\",\n        \"conflict\", \"resolution\", \"tension\", \"release\", \"suspense\",\n        \"beginning\", \"middle\", \"end\", \"cycle\", \"spiral\", \"fracture\",\n        \"homecoming\", \"exile\", \"return\", \"departure\", \"crossing\", \"threshold\",\n    ],\n    \"archetypes\": [\n        \"hero\", \"antihero\", \"villain\", \"mentor\", \"trickster\", \"shadow_self\",\n        \"guardian\", \"herald\", \"shapeshifter\", \"ally\", \"threshold_guardian\",\n        \"mother\", \"father\", \"child\", \"crone\", \"sage\", \"fool\",\n        \"outlaw\", \"lover\", \"ruler\", \"creator\", \"caretaker\", \"innocent\",\n        \"explorer\", \"rebel\", \"magician\", \"wanderer\",\n    ],\n    \"sensory\": [\n        \"light\", \"darkness\", \"shadow\", \"color\", \"sound\", \"silence\",\n        \"warmth\", \"cold\", \"texture\", \"taste\", \"smell\", \"weight\",\n        \"space\", \"distance\", \"depth\", \"surface\", \"edge\", \"boundary\",\n        \"motion\", \"stillness\", \"rhythm\", \"pulse\", \"breath\", \"heartbeat\",\n        \"flesh\", \"bone\", \"blood\", \"tears\", \"sweat\", \"skin\",\n        \"glow\", \"shimmer\", \"fade\", \"blur\", \"sharp\", \"soft\",\n    ],\n    \"mortality\": [\n        \"death\", \"life\", \"birth\", \"dying\", \"living\", \"end\",\n        \"ghost\", \"spirit\", \"soul\", \"body\", \"flesh\", \"bone\",\n        \"funeral\", \"waking\", \"sleep\", \"dream\", \"nightmare\", \"vision\",\n        \"sacred\", \"profane\", \"ritual\", \"prayer\", \"curse\", \"blessing\",\n        \"sacrifice\", \"altar\", \"threshold\", \"crossing\", \"passage\",\n    ],\n    \"relationships\": [\n        \"love\", \"hate\", \"desire\", \"need\", \"want\", \"devour\",\n        \"embrace\", \"push_away\", \"intimacy\", \"distance\", \"proximity\", \"absence\",\n        \"bond\", \"break\", \"repair\", \"trust\", \"betrayal\", \"loyalty\",\n        \"marriage\", \"divorce\", \"affair\", \"secret\", \"confession\", \"lie\",\n        \"parent\", \"child\", \"sibling\", \"stranger\", \"friend\", \"enemy\",\n        \"pursuit\", \"flight\", \"capture\", \"release\", \"chase\", \"escape\",\n    ],\n    \"cosmos\": [\n        \"order\", \"chaos\", \"creation\", \"destruction\", \"renewal\", \"entropy\",\n        \"law\", \"lawlessness\", \"structure\", \"fracture\", \"collapse\", \"foundation\",\n        \"balance\", \"imbalance\", \"equilibrium\", \"tipping_point\", \"critical_mass\",\n        \"power\", \"powerlessness\", \"control\", \"surrender\", \"domination\", \"submission\",\n        \"freedom\", \"confinement\", \"escape\", \"pursuit\", \"hiding\", \"exposure\",\n    ],\n    \"literary\": [\n        \"foreshadowing\", \"flashback\", \"unreliable_narrator\", \"frame_story\", \"motif\", \"leitmotif\",\n        \"allusion\", \"allegory\", \"personification\", \"metonymy\", \"synecdoche\", \"hyperbole\",\n        \"irony\", \"dramatic_irony\", \"situational_irony\", \"verbal_irony\", \"paradox\", \"oxymoron\",\n        \"juxtaposition\", \"anaphora\", \"epistrophe\", \"anastrophe\", \"enjambment\", \"stanzabreak\",\n        \"stream_of_consciousness\", \"free_verse\", \"prose\", \"paragraph\", \"chapter\", \"section\",\n    ],\n}\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# CROSS-CLUSTER RELATIONSHIPS\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nCROSS_CLUSTER_RELATIONSHIPS = [\n    (\"emotions\", \"relationships\", 0.8),\n    (\"emotions\", \"mortality\", 0.7),\n    (\"emotions\", \"sensory\", 0.6),\n    (\"emotions\", \"cosmos\", 0.4),\n    (\"narrative\", \"archetypes\", 0.8),\n    (\"narrative\", \"mortality\", 0.6),\n    (\"narrative\", \"cosmos\", 0.5),\n    (\"narrative\", \"relationships\", 0.5),\n    (\"creative\", \"emotions\", 0.7),\n    (\"creative\", \"sensory\", 0.5),\n    (\"creative\", \"literary\", 0.5),\n    (\"mortality\", \"relationships\", 0.6),\n    (\"mortality\", \"cosmos\", 0.5),\n    (\"cosmos\", \"creative\", 0.3),\n    (\"cosmos\", \"sensory\", 0.3),\n    (\"literary\", \"creative\", 0.5),\n]\n\nWITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT = 0.85\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# CREATIVE TENSIONS\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nCREATIVE_TENSIONS = [\n    (\"light\", \"darkness\", 0.95),\n    (\"creation\", \"destruction\", 0.95),\n    (\"love\", \"hate\", 0.90),\n    (\"order\", \"chaos\", 0.90),\n    (\"birth\", \"death\", 0.90),\n    (\"hope\", \"despair\", 0.85),\n    (\"truth\", \"lie\", 0.85),\n    (\"memory\", \"forgetting\", 0.80),\n    (\"homecoming\", \"exile\", 0.80),\n    (\"embrace\", \"push_away\", 0.80),\n    (\"isolation\", \"connection\", 0.75),\n    (\"rise\", \"fall\", 0.75),\n    (\"identity\", \"other\", 0.75),\n    (\"ghost\", \"flesh\", 0.70),\n    (\"sacred\", \"profane\", 0.70),\n    (\"retribution\", \"mercy\", 0.70),\n    (\"transformation\", \"stasis\", 0.65),\n    (\"confession\", \"secret\", 0.65),\n    (\"pursuit\", \"escape\", 0.65),\n    (\"intimacy\", \"distance\", 0.60),\n]\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# BUILD THEME ADJACENCY\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef build_thematic_graph(concepts, clusters):\n    concept_to_cluster = {}\n    for cluster_name, cluster_concepts in clusters.items():\n        for c in cluster_concepts:\n            if c not in concept_to_cluster:\n                concept_to_cluster[c] = cluster_name\n\n    cluster_to_weight = {}\n    for ca, cb, w in CROSS_CLUSTER_RELATIONSHIPS:\n        cluster_to_weight[(ca, cb)] = w\n        cluster_to_weight[(cb, ca)] = w\n\n    adjacencies = {}\n    all_concepts = [c for c in concepts if c in concept_to_cluster]\n\n    for i, c1 in enumerate(all_concepts):\n        for c2 in all_concepts[i+1:]:\n            ca, cb = concept_to_cluster.get(c1), concept_to_cluster.get(c2)\n            if ca == cb:\n                weight = WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n            elif ca and cb:\n                weight = cluster_to_weight.get((ca, cb), 0.1)\n            else:\n                weight = 0.05\n\n            if weight > 0:\n                adjacencies[(c1, c2)] = weight\n                adjacencies[(c2, c1)] = weight\n\n    return adjacencies\n\n\ndef build_creative_concept_universe():\n    all_concepts = []\n    for concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.values():\n        for c in concepts:\n            if c not in all_concepts:\n                all_concepts.append(c)\n\n    adjacency = build_thematic_graph(all_concepts, CONCEPT_CLUSTERS)\n\n    concept_to_cluster = {}\n    for cluster_name, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\n        for c in concepts:\n            concept_to_cluster[c] = cluster_name\n\n    nodes = {}\n    for concept in all_concepts:\n        cluster = concept_to_cluster.get(concept, \"unknown\")\n        base_activation = 0.5\n        if cluster == \"creative\":\n            base_activation = 0.7\n        elif cluster == \"emotions\":\n            base_activation = 0.6\n        nodes[concept] = {\n            \"concept\": concept,\n            \"cluster\": cluster,\n            \"base_activation\": base_activation,\n        }\n\n    return {\n        \"concepts\": all_concepts,\n        \"clusters\": CONCEPT_CLUSTERS,\n        \"adjacency\": adjacency,\n        \"nodes\": nodes,\n        \"num_concepts\": len(all_concepts),\n        \"tensions\": CREATIVE_TENSIONS,\n    }\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    print(\"BUILDING THEMATIC CONCEPT UNIVERSE\")\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n\n    universe = build_creative_concept_universe()\n    print(f\"Concepts: {universe['num_concepts']}\")\n    print(f\"Clusters: {len(universe['clusters'])}\")\n\n    adj = universe[\"adjacency\"]\n    weights = list(adj.values())\n    print(f\"Adjacencies: {len(weights)//2}\")\n    print(f\"Weight range: {min(weights):.2f} - {max(weights):.2f}\")\n\n    # Save with string keys for JSON\n    save_adj = {f\"{k[0]}||{k[1]}\": v for k, v in adj.items()}\n    save_universe = {\n        \"concepts\": universe[\"concepts\"],\n        \"clusters\": universe[\"clusters\"],\n        \"adjacency\": save_adj,\n        \"nodes\": universe[\"nodes\"],\n        \"num_concepts\": universe[\"num_concepts\"],\n        \"tensions\": CREATIVE_TENSIONS,\n    }\n\n    path = Path(__file__).parent / \"thematic_universe.json\"\n    with open(path, \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump(save_universe, f, indent=2)\n    print(f\"Saved to {path}\")\n\n    print()\n    print(\"Top tensions:\")\n    for a, b, w in CREATIVE_TENSIONS[:5]:\n        print(f\"  {a} <-> {b}: {w}\")\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774229440974}}
{"type":"message","id":"39d2067e","parentId":"0a710f38","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:30:40.992Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lo16178222cn_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nSPARK — Interactive Creative Writing Demo\nDrift Chamber + Thematic Graph + LLM → Creative Text\n\nUsage:\n    python demo.py                          # Interactive mode\n    python demo.py --domain romance --steering 0.3 --n 2  # Headless\n    python demo.py --ollama-url http://localhost:11434  # Use Ollama\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport sys\nimport argparse\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# Add drift-chamber to path\nDRIFT_PATH = Path(__file__).parent.parent / \"drift-chamber\"\nsys.path.insert(0, str(DRIFT_PATH))\n\nfrom drift_chamber import (\n    ConceptGraph, ConceptNode,\n    DriftChamberConfig,\n    drift_cycle, decay,\n    activation_entropy,\n)\n\nfrom spark.core.thematic_graph import CONCEPT_CLUSTERS, CREATIVE_TENSIONS, WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# THEME GRAPH BUILDER\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef build_thematic_graph(domain: str = \"all\") -> tuple:\n    \"\"\"\n    Build concept graph from thematic universe.\n    Returns (graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts)\n    \"\"\"\n    # Domain-specific concept selection\n    DOMAIN_CONFIGS = {\n        \"all\": {\n            \"clusters\": list(CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.keys()),\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"romance\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\", \"sensory\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"scifi\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"creative\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"creative\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"thriller\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"narrative\", \"relationships\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"narrative\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"literary\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"literary\", \"narrative\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\", \"literary\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"horror\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\", \"emotions\", \"cosmos\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"poetry\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"sensory\", \"literary\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\", \"sensory\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n    }\n\n    if domain not in DOMAIN_CONFIGS:\n        domain = \"all\"\n\n    config = DOMAIN_CONFIGS[domain]\n\n    # Select concepts\n    selected_concepts = []\n    for cluster_name in config[\"clusters\"]:\n        if cluster_name in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n            for concept in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster_name]:\n                if concept not in selected_concepts:\n                    selected_concepts.append(concept)\n\n    # Build concept_to_cluster\n    concept_to_cluster = {}\n    for cluster_name, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\n        for c in concepts:\n            if c not in concept_to_cluster:\n                concept_to_cluster[c] = cluster_name\n\n    # Build adjacency\n    CROSS_WEIGHTS = {\n        (\"emotions\", \"relationships\"): 0.8,\n        (\"emotions\", \"sensory\"): 0.6,\n        (\"narrative\", \"archetypes\"): 0.8,\n        (\"creative\", \"emotions\"): 0.7,\n        (\"creative\", \"sensory\"): 0.5,\n        (\"mortality\", \"emotions\"): 0.7,\n        (\"cosmos\", \"creative\"): 0.3,\n    }\n\n    adj = {}\n    for c1 in selected_concepts:\n        for c2 in selected_concepts:\n            if c1 >= c2:\n                continue\n            ca = concept_to_cluster.get(c1, \"\")\n            cb = concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")\n            if ca == cb:\n                w = WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n            else:\n                w = CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((ca, cb), CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((cb, ca), 0.1))\n            if w > 0:\n                adj[(c1, c2)] = w\n                adj[(c2, c1)] = w\n\n    # Build graph\n    graph = ConceptGraph(seed=42)\n    for c in selected_concepts:\n        graph.add_node(ConceptNode(id=c, activation=0.5))\n\n    for (a, b), w in adj.items():\n        graph.add_edge(a, b, w)\n        graph.add_edge(b, a, w)\n\n    # Goal concepts\n    goal_concepts = set()\n    for cluster_name in config[\"goal_clusters\"]:\n        if cluster_name in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n            for c in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster_name]:\n                if c in selected_concepts:\n                    goal_concepts.add(c)\n\n    return graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, selected_concepts\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# DRIFT RUNNER\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef run_drift(\n    graph: ConceptGraph,\n    concept_to_cluster: dict,\n    goal_concepts: set,\n    steering: float = 0.3,\n    steps: int = 30,\n    diffusion_rate: float = 0.1,\n    decay_rate: float = 0.02,\n) -> tuple:\n    \"\"\"\n    Run drift cycle on the thematic graph.\n    Returns (final_graph, top_concepts, activation_history)\n    \"\"\"\n    # Initialize: goal-adjacent HIGH, others LOW\n    for node in graph.nodes.values():\n        if node.id in goal_concepts:\n            node.activation = 0.95\n        else:\n            cluster = concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\")\n            if cluster in [\"emotions\", \"relationships\"]:\n                node.activation = 0.5\n            else:\n                node.activation = 0.05\n\n    config = DriftChamberConfig(\n        steering_strength=steering,\n        diffusion_rate=diffusion_rate,\n        decay_rate=decay_rate,\n        seed=42,\n        max_steps=steps,\n    )\n\n    history = []\n    for step in range(steps):\n        _, graph = drift_cycle(graph, None, config)\n        graph = decay(graph, rate=decay_rate)\n        history.append({\n            \"step\": step,\n            \"mean_activation\": sum(n.activation for n in graph.nodes.values()) / len(graph.nodes),\n            \"strong_nodes\": len(graph.get_strong_nodes(0.3)),\n        })\n\n    return graph, history\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# TEXT GENERATION\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef generate_text(\n    top_concepts: list,\n    theme: str,\n    mode: str = \"creative\",\n    ollama_url: str = None,\n    model: str = \"llama2:7b\",\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Map top concepts to creative text using LLM.\n    Falls back to a poetic concept description if no LLM available.\n    \"\"\"\n    if ollama_url:\n        try:\n            import requests\n            top_15 = top_concepts[:15]\n            mid_10 = top_concepts[15:25]\n\n            prompts = {\n                \"creative\": f\"\"\"You are a literary fiction writer. Write a short piece (150-200 words) exploring the theme: \"{theme}\".\n\nIncorporate these ideas naturally into the texture of the prose — not as a list, but woven in:\nPrimary: {', '.join(top_15)}\nSecondary: {', '.join(mid_10) if mid_10 else 'none'}\n\nThe piece should feel surprising and alive. Avoid clichés. End with resonance, not resolution.\"\"\",\n\n                \"divergent\": f\"\"\"Write a brief, experimental fragment (100-150 words) on the theme: \"{theme}\".\n\nSubvert expectations. Use these ideas: {', '.join(top_15)}\n\nBe strange. Be unexpected. The piece should make the reader see something familiar in a new way.\"\"\",\n\n                \"exploratory\": f\"\"\"Write a contemplative piece (150-200 words) on the theme: \"{theme}\".\n\nExplore with care. Consider: {', '.join(top_15)}\nAnd: {', '.join(mid_10) if mid_10 else 'none'}\n\nThe piece should feel precise and carefully observed.\"\"\",\n            }\n\n            payload = {\n                \"model\": model,\n                \"prompt\": prompts.get(mode, prompts[\"creative\"]),\n                \"stream\": False,\n                \"options\": {\"temperature\": 0.8, \"num_predict\": 400},\n            }\n\n            r = requests.post(f\"{ollama_url}/api/generate\", json=payload, timeout=60)\n            if r.status_code == 200:\n                return r.json().get(\"response\", \"\").strip()\n            else:\n                return f\"[LLM error: {r.status_code}]\"\n\n        except Exception as e:\n            return f\"[LLM unavailable: {e}]\"\n\n    else:\n        # Fallback: poetic concept description\n        top_10 = top_concepts[:10]\n        pieces = []\n        for i, concept in enumerate(top_10):\n            tension = next(((a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS if a == concept or b == concept), None)\n            if tension:\n                pieces.append(f\"the {concept} of {tension[1] if tension[0] == concept else tension[0]}\")\n            else:\n                pieces.append(concept)\n\n        return f\"\"\"THEMATIC CONCEPT CLUSTER — \"{theme.upper()}\"\n\nPrimary concepts: {', '.join(top_10)}\n\nCreative tensions at work:\n{\"\".join(f\"  • {p}\\n\" for p in pieces)}\n\nThese concepts, arranged through the drift chamber at this steering strength,\nform a thematic constellation around the theme of {theme}.\n\n[Connect to Ollama at --ollama-url to generate full prose]\n\"\"\"\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# INTERACTIVE MODE\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef print_banner():\n    print()\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    print(\"  SPARK — Interactive Creative Writing Demo\")\n    print(\"  Drift Chamber + Thematic Graph + LLM\")\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    print()\n\n\ndef print_domains():\n    print(\"Available domains:\")\n    for domain in [\"all\", \"romance\", \"scifi\", \"thriller\", \"literary\", \"horror\", \"poetry\"]:\n        desc = {\n            \"all\": \"All creative concepts\",\n            \"romance\": \"Love, longing, connection, loss\",\n            \"scifi\": \"Technology, cosmos, humanity, creation\",\n            \"thriller\": \"Tension, power, pursuit, secrets\",\n            \"literary\": \"Craft, meaning, form, expression\",\n            \"horror\": \"Death, dread, flesh, threshold\",\n            \"poetry\": \"Sensory, image, rhythm, metaphor\",\n        }[domain]\n        print(f\"  {domain:12s} — {desc}\")\n    print()\n\n\ndef print_modes():\n    print(\"Modes:\")\n    for mode in [\"creative\", \"divergent\", \"exploratory\"]:\n        desc = {\n            \"creative\": \"Balanced: coherent + exploratory\",\n            \"divergent\": \"Maximum surprise, subverts expectations\",\n            \"exploratory\": \"Contemplative, carefully observed\",\n        }[mode]\n        print(f\"  {mode:12s} — {desc}\")\n    print()\n\n\ndef interactive():\n    print_banner()\n    print_domains()\n    print_modes()\n\n    # Get user choices\n    domain = input(\"Domain [all]: \").strip().lower() or \"all\"\n    theme = input(\"Theme [love in the age of AI]: \").strip() or \"love in the age of AI\"\n    steering = float(input(\"Steering strength [0.3]: \").strip() or \"0.3\")\n    mode = input(\"Mode [creative]: \").strip().lower() or \"creative\"\n    n_outputs = int(input(\"Number of outputs [2]: \").strip() or \"2\")\n    ollama_url = input(\"Ollama URL (Enter to skip) [none]: \").strip() or None\n    if ollama_url and not ollama_url.startswith(\"http\"):\n        ollama_url = f\"http://{ollama_url}\"\n\n    print()\n    print(f\"Building {domain} concept graph...\")\n    graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, concepts = build_thematic_graph(domain)\n    print(f\"  {len(graph.nodes)} concepts, {sum(len(n.neighbors) for n in graph.nodes.values())//2} edges\")\n\n    print(f\"Running drift (steering={steering}, steps=30)...\")\n    graph, history = run_drift(graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, steering=steering)\n    print(f\"  Final: {len(graph.get_strong_nodes(0.3))} strong concepts\")\n\n    # Get top concepts\n    sorted_nodes = sorted(graph.nodes.values(), key=lambda n: n.activation, reverse=True)\n    top_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[:20]]\n    top_clusters = [concept_to_cluster.get(c, \"unknown\") for c in top_concepts]\n\n    print()\n    print(\"TOP 20 ACTIVATED CONCEPTS:\")\n    for i, (c, cluster) in enumerate(zip(top_concepts[:10], top_clusters[:10])):\n        act = sorted_nodes[i].activation\n        bar = \"█\" * int(act * 20)\n        print(f\"  {i+1:2d}. {c:20s} [{cluster:12s}] {bar} {act:.2f}\")\n    if len(top_concepts) > 10:\n        print(f\"  ... and {len(top_concepts)-10} more\")\n    print()\n\n    # Generate text\n    for i in range(n_outputs):\n        print(f\"\\n--- OUTPUT {i+1}/{n_outputs} ---\\n\")\n        text = generate_text(top_concepts, theme, mode, ollama_url)\n        print(text)\n        print()\n\n    print(f\"\\nRegenerated concepts: python demo.py --domain {domain} --steering {steering} --mode {mode} --ollama-url {ollama_url or ''}\")\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# MAIN\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"SPARK Interactive Creative Writing Demo\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--domain\", default=\"all\", choices=[\"all\", \"romance\", \"scifi\", \"thriller\", \"literary\", \"horror\", \"poetry\"])\n    parser.add_argument(\"--theme\", default=\"love in the age of AI\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--steering\", type=float, default=0.3)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--mode\", default=\"creative\", choices=[\"creative\", \"divergent\", \"exploratory\"])\n    parser.add_argument(\"--n\", type=int, default=2, help=\"Number of outputs\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--ollama-url\", default=None, help=\"Ollama API URL\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--interactive\", action=\"store_true\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--list-domains\", action=\"store_true\")\n\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    if args.list_domains:\n        print_banner()\n        print_domains()\n        print_modes()\n        return\n\n    # Build graph\n    graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, concepts = build_thematic_graph(args.domain)\n    print(f\"[SPARK] {args.domain} graph: {len(graph.nodes)} concepts, {sum(len(n.neighbors) for n in graph.nodes.values())//2} edges\")\n    print(f\"[SPARK] Steering: {args.steering}, Mode: {args.mode}\")\n\n    # Run drift\n    graph, history = run_drift(graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, steering=args.steering)\n    strong = len(graph.get_strong_nodes(0.3))\n    print(f\"[SPARK] Drift complete: {strong} strong concepts | entropy: {activation_entropy(graph):.3f}\")\n\n    # Get top concepts\n    sorted_nodes = sorted(graph.nodes.values(), key=lambda n: n.activation, reverse=True)\n    top_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[:20]]\n\n    print(f\"[SPARK] Top 10: {', '.join(top_concepts[:10])}\")\n\n    # Generate\n    for i in range(args.n):\n        print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\\nOUTPUT {i+1}/{args.n}\\n{'='*60}\")\n        text = generate_text(top_concepts, args.theme, args.mode, args.ollama_url)\n        print(text)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if len(sys.argv) == 1 or \"--interactive\" in sys.argv:\n        interactive()\n    else:\n        main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774229440981}}
{"type":"message","id":"e910e62d","parentId":"39d2067e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:30:59.981Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture. Let me trace through what happened when Zach used SPARK:\n\n1. `demo.py` is the main entry point\n2. It builds a thematic graph from `CONCEPT_CLUSTERS` \n3. Runs drift on the graph\n4. Then calls `generate_text()` which:\n   - If `ollama_url` is set → calls Ollama with a prompt that includes the theme + top concepts\n   - If no `ollama_url` → shows a poetic concept description (the fallback)\n\nThe problem is clear now: `generate_text()` is making a single LLM call with a generic prompt. The prompt does include the top concepts, but it's:\n\n\n- Still following the Hallmark template structure (\"You are a literary fiction writer. Write a short piece (150-200 words) exploring the theme:...\")\n- NOT actually using the drift path to create unexpected thematic connections\n- NOT sampling concepts based on their activation strength in a sophisticated way\n- Just listing concepts and asking the LLM to \"incorporate\" them\n\nThe real issue is that this approach ignores what actually makes the Drift Chamber novel—the temporal progression through concept activations. The drift path itself should be encoded in the generation, not just the final concept list.\n\nLooking at the Ollama prompt, it's doing the same thing: asking for a generic 150-200 word piece with a list of primary and secondary concepts, topped with a cliché ending instruction. It's superficial concept incorporation rather than structural thematic exploration.\n\nBut here's the critical problem: there's no user context being passed in at all. Zach mentioned \"me at homeless guy with a nametag\" in the chat, yet the SPARK demo treats it as just another concept to add to the list. The `theme` parameter is hardcoded to \"love in the age of AI\" by default, so even if Zach provided that context, it's being overridden. The system isn't actually capturing what the user wanted—it just processed the demo's static theme instead.\n\nNow I need to check how drift-chamber actually works to understand where the disconnect happened.","thinkingSignature":"3d7e8a964c4b66588af151b18ef7c12a681f5d11f45fbd09898a65dae3100dc5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aoscwuf0z10y_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/drift-chamber\" -Recurse -Include \"*.py\",\"*.md\",\"*.json\" | Where-Object { $_.FullName -notmatch \"__pycache__|node_modules|\\.git\" } | Select-Object FullName, Length | Format-Table -AutoSize"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42087,"output":520,"cacheRead":12730,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55337,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774229440993}}
