{"type":"message","id":"f3a806fb","parentId":"ee897947","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:33:26.142Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me update `demo.py` to capture the user's seed concept/moment and pass it through. The demo.py needs to be more interactive and actually use Zach's input.\n\nLet me also check if there's a way to actually run SPARK with Zach's input. Looking at the demo.py, when you run it in interactive mode, it prompts for domain, theme, steering, mode, n_outputs, and ollama_url. The \"theme\" is the only thing you can set interactively. The user's seed moment (like \"me at homeless guy with a nametag\") isn't captured at all.\n\nI need to:\n1. Add a \"seed moment\" input to the interactive demo\n\n\n2. Pass it through to `generate_text()` which needs to accept it as a parameter\n3. Pass it to the mapper\n\nThe `generate_text()` function in demo.py currently doesn't accept a seed_moment parameter, so I'll need to add that flow through the entire chain.","thinkingSignature":"f323c88d035866076abcdc7863dff5bb11329af5839382f87bd4cf15d99fdcbf"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me update `demo.py` to capture the user's seed moment and actually use it:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t54lgsuhgca5_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":1,"limit":80,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\demo.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":56859,"output":279,"cacheRead":12730,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69868,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774229596810}}
{"type":"message","id":"41064bb8","parentId":"f3a806fb","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:33:26.167Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_t54lgsuhgca5_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nSPARK — Interactive Creative Writing Demo\nDrift Chamber + Thematic Graph + LLM → Creative Text\n\nUsage:\n    python demo.py                          # Interactive mode\n    python demo.py --domain romance --steering 0.3 --n 2  # Headless\n    python demo.py --ollama-url http://localhost:11434  # Use Ollama\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport sys\nimport argparse\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# Add drift-chamber to path\nDRIFT_PATH = Path(__file__).parent.parent / \"drift-chamber\"\nsys.path.insert(0, str(DRIFT_PATH))\n\nfrom drift_chamber import (\n    ConceptGraph, ConceptNode,\n    DriftChamberConfig,\n    drift_cycle, decay,\n    activation_entropy,\n)\n\nfrom spark.core.thematic_graph import CONCEPT_CLUSTERS, CREATIVE_TENSIONS, WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# THEME GRAPH BUILDER\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef build_thematic_graph(domain: str = \"all\") -> tuple:\n    \"\"\"\n    Build concept graph from thematic universe.\n    Returns (graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts)\n    \"\"\"\n    # Domain-specific concept selection\n    DOMAIN_CONFIGS = {\n        \"all\": {\n            \"clusters\": list(CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.keys()),\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"romance\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\", \"sensory\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"scifi\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"creative\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"creative\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"thriller\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"narrative\", \"relationships\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"narrative\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"literary\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"literary\", \"narrative\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\", \"literary\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"horror\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\", \"emotions\", \"cosmos\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"poetry\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"sensory\", \"literary\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\", \"sensory\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n    }\n\n    if domain not in DOMAIN_CONFIGS:\n        domain = \"all\"\n\n[340 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774229606156}}
{"type":"message","id":"c74559ce","parentId":"41064bb8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:33:29.878Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the rest of the demo.py file, focusing on the generate_text function and the interactive mode.","thinkingSignature":"57b2c7eff00086128fe264d43351a3df2a9ac7a0550c299ef422b0f039396ad5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ygihhsbvgt80_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":81,"limit":260,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\demo.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":57743,"output":84,"cacheRead":12730,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70557,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774229606170}}
{"type":"message","id":"a9c3bc31","parentId":"c74559ce","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:33:29.891Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ygihhsbvgt80_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n    config = DOMAIN_CONFIGS[domain]\n\n    # Select concepts\n    selected_concepts = []\n    for cluster_name in config[\"clusters\"]:\n        if cluster_name in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n            for concept in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster_name]:\n                if concept not in selected_concepts:\n                    selected_concepts.append(concept)\n\n    # Build concept_to_cluster\n    concept_to_cluster = {}\n    for cluster_name, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\n        for c in concepts:\n            if c not in concept_to_cluster:\n                concept_to_cluster[c] = cluster_name\n\n    # Build adjacency\n    CROSS_WEIGHTS = {\n        (\"emotions\", \"relationships\"): 0.8,\n        (\"emotions\", \"sensory\"): 0.6,\n        (\"narrative\", \"archetypes\"): 0.8,\n        (\"creative\", \"emotions\"): 0.7,\n        (\"creative\", \"sensory\"): 0.5,\n        (\"mortality\", \"emotions\"): 0.7,\n        (\"cosmos\", \"creative\"): 0.3,\n    }\n\n    adj = {}\n    for c1 in selected_concepts:\n        for c2 in selected_concepts:\n            if c1 >= c2:\n                continue\n            ca = concept_to_cluster.get(c1, \"\")\n            cb = concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")\n            if ca == cb:\n                w = WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n            else:\n                w = CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((ca, cb), CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((cb, ca), 0.1))\n            if w > 0:\n                adj[(c1, c2)] = w\n                adj[(c2, c1)] = w\n\n    # Build graph\n    graph = ConceptGraph(seed=42)\n    for c in selected_concepts:\n        graph.add_node(ConceptNode(id=c, activation=0.5))\n\n    for (a, b), w in adj.items():\n        graph.add_edge(a, b, w)\n        graph.add_edge(b, a, w)\n\n    # Goal concepts\n    goal_concepts = set()\n    for cluster_name in config[\"goal_clusters\"]:\n        if cluster_name in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n            for c in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster_name]:\n                if c in selected_concepts:\n                    goal_concepts.add(c)\n\n    return graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, selected_concepts\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# DRIFT RUNNER\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef run_drift(\n    graph: ConceptGraph,\n    concept_to_cluster: dict,\n    goal_concepts: set,\n    steering: float = 0.3,\n    steps: int = 30,\n    diffusion_rate: float = 0.1,\n    decay_rate: float = 0.02,\n) -> tuple:\n    \"\"\"\n    Run drift cycle on the thematic graph.\n    Returns (final_graph, top_concepts, activation_history)\n    \"\"\"\n    # Initialize: goal-adjacent HIGH, others LOW\n    for node in graph.nodes.values():\n        if node.id in goal_concepts:\n            node.activation = 0.95\n        else:\n            cluster = concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\")\n            if cluster in [\"emotions\", \"relationships\"]:\n                node.activation = 0.5\n            else:\n                node.activation = 0.05\n\n    config = DriftChamberConfig(\n        steering_strength=steering,\n        diffusion_rate=diffusion_rate,\n        decay_rate=decay_rate,\n        seed=42,\n        max_steps=steps,\n    )\n\n    history = []\n    for step in range(steps):\n        _, graph = drift_cycle(graph, None, config)\n        graph = decay(graph, rate=decay_rate)\n        history.append({\n            \"step\": step,\n            \"mean_activation\": sum(n.activation for n in graph.nodes.values()) / len(graph.nodes),\n            \"strong_nodes\": len(graph.get_strong_nodes(0.3)),\n        })\n\n    return graph, history\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# TEXT GENERATION\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef generate_text(\n    top_concepts: list,\n    theme: str,\n    mode: str = \"creative\",\n    ollama_url: str = None,\n    model: str = \"llama2:7b\",\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Map top concepts to creative text using LLM.\n    Falls back to a poetic concept description if no LLM available.\n    \"\"\"\n    if ollama_url:\n        try:\n            import requests\n            top_15 = top_concepts[:15]\n            mid_10 = top_concepts[15:25]\n\n            prompts = {\n                \"creative\": f\"\"\"You are a literary fiction writer. Write a short piece (150-200 words) exploring the theme: \"{theme}\".\n\nIncorporate these ideas naturally into the texture of the prose — not as a list, but woven in:\nPrimary: {', '.join(top_15)}\nSecondary: {', '.join(mid_10) if mid_10 else 'none'}\n\nThe piece should feel surprising and alive. Avoid clichés. End with resonance, not resolution.\"\"\",\n\n                \"divergent\": f\"\"\"Write a brief, experimental fragment (100-150 words) on the theme: \"{theme}\".\n\nSubvert expectations. Use these ideas: {', '.join(top_15)}\n\nBe strange. Be unexpected. The piece should make the reader see something familiar in a new way.\"\"\",\n\n                \"exploratory\": f\"\"\"Write a contemplative piece (150-200 words) on the theme: \"{theme}\".\n\nExplore with care. Consider: {', '.join(top_15)}\nAnd: {', '.join(mid_10) if mid_10 else 'none'}\n\nThe piece should feel precise and carefully observed.\"\"\",\n            }\n\n            payload = {\n                \"model\": model,\n                \"prompt\": prompts.get(mode, prompts[\"creative\"]),\n                \"stream\": False,\n                \"options\": {\"temperature\": 0.8, \"num_predict\": 400},\n            }\n\n            r = requests.post(f\"{ollama_url}/api/generate\", json=payload, timeout=60)\n            if r.status_code == 200:\n                return r.json().get(\"response\", \"\").strip()\n            else:\n                return f\"[LLM error: {r.status_code}]\"\n\n        except Exception as e:\n            return f\"[LLM unavailable: {e}]\"\n\n    else:\n        # Fallback: poetic concept description\n        top_10 = top_concepts[:10]\n        pieces = []\n        for i, concept in enumerate(top_10):\n            tension = next(((a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS if a == concept or b == concept), None)\n            if tension:\n                pieces.append(f\"the {concept} of {tension[1] if tension[0] == concept else tension[0]}\")\n            else:\n                pieces.append(concept)\n\n        return f\"\"\"THEMATIC CONCEPT CLUSTER — \"{theme.upper()}\"\n\nPrimary concepts: {', '.join(top_10)}\n\nCreative tensions at work:\n{\"\".join(f\"  • {p}\\n\" for p in pieces)}\n\nThese concepts, arranged through the drift chamber at this steering strength,\nform a thematic constellation around the theme of {theme}.\n\n[Connect to Ollama at --ollama-url to generate full prose]\n\"\"\"\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# INTERACTIVE MODE\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef print_banner():\n    print()\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    print(\"  SPARK — Interactive Creative Writing Demo\")\n    print(\"  Drift Chamber + Thematic Graph + LLM\")\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    print()\n\n\ndef print_domains():\n    print(\"Available domains:\")\n    for domain in [\"all\", \"romance\", \"scifi\", \"thriller\", \"literary\", \"horror\", \"poetry\"]:\n        desc = {\n            \"all\": \"All creative concepts\",\n            \"romance\": \"Love, longing, connection, loss\",\n            \"scifi\": \"Technology, cosmos, humanity, creation\",\n            \"thriller\": \"Tension, power, pursuit, secrets\",\n            \"literary\": \"Craft, meaning, form, expression\",\n            \"horror\": \"Death, dread, flesh, threshold\",\n            \"poetry\": \"Sensory, image, rhythm, metaphor\",\n        }[domain]\n        print(f\"  {domain:12s} — {desc}\")\n    print()\n\n\ndef print_modes():\n    print(\"Modes:\")\n    for mode in [\"creative\", \"divergent\", \"exploratory\"]:\n        desc = {\n            \"creative\": \"Balanced: coherent + exploratory\",\n            \"divergent\": \"Maximum surprise, subverts expectations\",\n            \"exploratory\": \"Contemplative, carefully observed\",\n        }[mode]\n        print(f\"  {mode:12s} — {desc}\")\n    print()\n\n\ndef interactive():\n    print_banner()\n    print_domains()\n    print_modes()\n\n    # Get user choices\n    domain = input(\"Domain [all]: \").strip().lower() or \"all\"\n    theme = input(\"Theme [love in the age of AI]: \").strip() or \"love in the age of AI\"\n    steering = float(input(\"Steering strength [0.3]: \").strip() or \"0.3\")\n    mode = input(\"Mode [creative]: \").strip().lower() or \"creative\"\n    n_outputs = int(input(\"Number of outputs [2]: \").strip() or \"2\")\n    ollama_url = input(\"Ollama URL (Enter to skip) [none]: \").strip() or None\n    if ollama_url and not ollama_url.startswith(\"http\"):\n        ollama_url = f\"http://{ollama_url}\"\n\n    print()\n    print(f\"Building {domain} concept graph...\")\n    graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, concepts = build_thematic_graph(domain)\n    print(f\"  {len(graph.nodes)} concepts, {sum(len(n.neighbors) for n in graph.nodes.values())//2} edges\")\n\n    print(f\"Running drift (steering={steering}, steps=30)...\")\n\n[80 more lines in file. Use offset=341 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774229609886}}
{"type":"message","id":"5126c6a2","parentId":"a9c3bc31","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:33:37.740Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. The `generate_text()` function in demo.py is completely separate from the `CreativeMapper` class in `llm_mapper.py`. They're not even using the same code! The demo.py has its own hardcoded prompts that are the Hallmark ones, while I rewrote `llm_mapper.py` with the new good prompts.\n\nThe fix needs to:\n1. Make `demo.py` use the new `CreativeMapper` from `llm_mapper.py` \n2. Add a seed_moment parameter to the interactive flow\n3. The drift path should be passed through properly\n\n\n4. I need to update the demo.py to wire everything together correctly—use the CreativeMapper class with the seed_moment parameter, pass the drift path through, and update the CLI arguments to support it all.","thinkingSignature":"e80dab6277d9cb5a7ba2f8e59c1568b641f3b3576d19e1e797cc02623f5e9da8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rpazgb2p1pg4_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":341,"limit":100,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\demo.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":59986,"output":232,"cacheRead":12730,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72948,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774229609893}}
{"type":"message","id":"9629c120","parentId":"5126c6a2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:33:37.750Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rpazgb2p1pg4_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    graph, history = run_drift(graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, steering=steering)\n    print(f\"  Final: {len(graph.get_strong_nodes(0.3))} strong concepts\")\n\n    # Get top concepts\n    sorted_nodes = sorted(graph.nodes.values(), key=lambda n: n.activation, reverse=True)\n    top_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[:20]]\n    top_clusters = [concept_to_cluster.get(c, \"unknown\") for c in top_concepts]\n\n    print()\n    print(\"TOP 20 ACTIVATED CONCEPTS:\")\n    for i, (c, cluster) in enumerate(zip(top_concepts[:10], top_clusters[:10])):\n        act = sorted_nodes[i].activation\n        bar = \"█\" * int(act * 20)\n        print(f\"  {i+1:2d}. {c:20s} [{cluster:12s}] {bar} {act:.2f}\")\n    if len(top_concepts) > 10:\n        print(f\"  ... and {len(top_concepts)-10} more\")\n    print()\n\n    # Generate text\n    for i in range(n_outputs):\n        print(f\"\\n--- OUTPUT {i+1}/{n_outputs} ---\\n\")\n        text = generate_text(top_concepts, theme, mode, ollama_url)\n        print(text)\n        print()\n\n    print(f\"\\nRegenerated concepts: python demo.py --domain {domain} --steering {steering} --mode {mode} --ollama-url {ollama_url or ''}\")\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# MAIN\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"SPARK Interactive Creative Writing Demo\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--domain\", default=\"all\", choices=[\"all\", \"romance\", \"scifi\", \"thriller\", \"literary\", \"horror\", \"poetry\"])\n    parser.add_argument(\"--theme\", default=\"love in the age of AI\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--steering\", type=float, default=0.3)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--mode\", default=\"creative\", choices=[\"creative\", \"divergent\", \"exploratory\"])\n    parser.add_argument(\"--n\", type=int, default=2, help=\"Number of outputs\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--ollama-url\", default=None, help=\"Ollama API URL\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--interactive\", action=\"store_true\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--list-domains\", action=\"store_true\")\n\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    if args.list_domains:\n        print_banner()\n        print_domains()\n        print_modes()\n        return\n\n    # Build graph\n    graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, concepts = build_thematic_graph(args.domain)\n    print(f\"[SPARK] {args.domain} graph: {len(graph.nodes)} concepts, {sum(len(n.neighbors) for n in graph.nodes.values())//2} edges\")\n    print(f\"[SPARK] Steering: {args.steering}, Mode: {args.mode}\")\n\n    # Run drift\n    graph, history = run_drift(graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, steering=args.steering)\n    strong = len(graph.get_strong_nodes(0.3))\n    print(f\"[SPARK] Drift complete: {strong} strong concepts | entropy: {activation_entropy(graph):.3f}\")\n\n    # Get top concepts\n    sorted_nodes = sorted(graph.nodes.values(), key=lambda n: n.activation, reverse=True)\n    top_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[:20]]\n\n    print(f\"[SPARK] Top 10: {', '.join(top_concepts[:10])}\")\n\n    # Generate\n    for i in range(args.n):\n        print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\\nOUTPUT {i+1}/{args.n}\\n{'='*60}\")\n        text = generate_text(top_concepts, args.theme, args.mode, args.ollama_url)\n        print(text)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if len(sys.argv) == 1 or \"--interactive\" in sys.argv:\n        interactive()\n    else:\n        main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774229617746}}
{"type":"message","id":"258a6dfe","parentId":"9629c120","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:34:09.843Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full structure. The `generate_text()` function in demo.py is standalone and has its own Hallmark prompts. I need to:\n\n1. Replace `generate_text()` in demo.py with the `CreativeMapper` class that I already rewrote\n2. Add `--seed-moment` parameter\n3. Wire up the drift path to be passed through\n4. Make the mapper work with Ollama (it currently doesn't support it directly)\n\nBut wait - the `CreativeMapper` class in `llm_mapper.py` already supports Ollama! It has:\n```python\nelif provider == \"ollama\":\n    import requests\n    response = requests.post(\n        \"http://localhost:11434/api/generate\",\n        ...\n```\n\nSo the new `CreativeMapper` supports Ollama. The issue is `generate_text()` in demo.py doesn't use `CreativeMapper` at all - it has its own standalone requests call with Hallmark prompts.\n\nNow I need to decide: should I update demo.py to use CreativeMapper, or should I update the generate_text() function within demo.py to use the new prompts?\n\nThe cleanest approach is to update demo.py to use CreativeMapper, which will automatically pick up the new prompt structure and Ollama support. But the API is different - CreativeMapper.map_concepts_to_text takes a dict of concept activations, while demo.py's generate_text takes a list of top_concepts. I'll need to bridge this: convert the list to a dict with activation scores, then pass it to CreativeMapper.\n\nCreativeMapper already has the seed_moment and user_constraints parameters I added. So I can update demo.py's generate_text function to use CreativeMapper internally, converting the concept list into the activation dict format that map_concepts_to_text expects.","thinkingSignature":"2bf77d12b33f7b54eb821d607fb54b63853dbfdf07059d6da1845cfc94f8add3"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll rewrite the `generate_text` function in demo.py to use `CreativeMapper` (which now has the good prompts), and add seed moment support:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8itqnvssh0ro_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\demo.py","oldText":"# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# TEXT GENERATION\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef generate_text(\n    top_concepts: list,\n    theme: str,\n    mode: str = \"creative\",\n    ollama_url: str = None,\n    model: str = \"llama2:7b\",\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Map top concepts to creative text using LLM.\n    Falls back to a poetic concept description if no LLM available.\n    \"\"\"\n    if ollama_url:\n        try:\n            import requests\n            top_15 = top_concepts[:15]\n            mid_10 = top_concepts[15:25]\n\n            prompts = {\n                \"creative\": f\"\"\"You are a literary fiction writer. Write a short piece (150-200 words) exploring the theme: \"{theme}\".\n\nIncorporate these ideas naturally into the texture of the prose — not as a list, but woven in:\nPrimary: {', '.join(top_15)}\nSecondary: {', '.join(mid_10) if mid_10 else 'none'}\n\nThe piece should feel surprising and alive. Avoid clichés. End with resonance, not resolution.\"\"\",\n\n                \"divergent\": f\"\"\"Write a brief, experimental fragment (100-150 words) on the theme: \"{theme}\".\n\nSubvert expectations. Use these ideas: {', '.join(top_15)}\n\nBe strange. Be unexpected. The piece should make the reader see something familiar in a new way.\"\"\",\n\n                \"exploratory\": f\"\"\"Write a contemplative piece (150-200 words) on the theme: \"{theme}\".\n\nExplore with care. Consider: {', '.join(top_15)}\nAnd: {', '.join(mid_10) if mid_10 else 'none'}\n\nThe piece should feel precise and carefully observed.\"\"\",\n            }\n\n            payload = {\n                \"model\": model,\n                \"prompt\": prompts.get(mode, prompts[\"creative\"]),\n                \"stream\": False,\n                \"options\": {\"temperature\": 0.8, \"num_predict\": 400},\n            }\n\n            r = requests.post(f\"{ollama_url}/api/generate\", json=payload, timeout=60)\n            if r.status_code == 200:\n                return r.json().get(\"response\", \"\").strip()\n            else:\n                return f\"[LLM error: {r.status_code}]\"\n\n        except Exception as e:\n            return f\"[LLM unavailable: {e}]\"\n\n    else:\n        # Fallback: poetic concept description\n        top_10 = top_concepts[:10]\n        pieces = []\n        for i, concept in enumerate(top_10):\n            tension = next(((a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS if a == concept or b == concept), None)\n            if tension:\n                pieces.append(f\"the {concept} of {tension[1] if tension[0] == concept else tension[0]}\")\n            else:\n                pieces.append(concept)\n\n        return f\"\"\"THEMATIC CONCEPT CLUSTER — \"{theme.upper()}\"\n\nPrimary concepts: {', '.join(top_10)}\n\nCreative tensions at work:\n{\"\".join(f\"  • {p}\\n\" for p in pieces)}\n\nThese concepts, arranged through the drift chamber at this steering strength,\nform a thematic constellation around the theme of {theme}.\n\n[Connect to Ollama at --ollama-url to generate full prose]\n\"\"\"","new_string":"# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# TEXT GENERATION — uses CreativeMapper from llm_mapper.py\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef generate_text(\n    top_concepts: list,\n    theme: str,\n    mode: str = \"creative\",\n    ollama_url: str = None,\n    model: str = \"qwen2.5:7b\",\n    seed_moment: str = None,\n    user_constraints: list = None,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Map top concepts to creative text using CreativeMapper.\n    Falls back to a poetic concept description if no LLM available.\n    \n    Args:\n        top_concepts: Ordered list of concept names (first = highest activation)\n        theme: The driving theme\n        mode: creative | divergent | exploratory\n        ollama_url: Ollama API URL (if None, uses OpenAI/Anthropic env vars)\n        model: Model name for Ollama\n        seed_moment: A specific moment/detail/seed text to anchor the piece\n        user_constraints: List of elements the user wants in the piece\n    \"\"\"\n    # Import CreativeMapper lazily\n    try:\n        from spark.core.llm_mapper import CreativeMapper, find_tensions_in_concepts, sample_drift_path\n    except ImportError:\n        return \"[ERROR: Could not import CreativeMapper. Run from spark/ directory or check PYTHONPATH.]\"\n\n    # Build activation dict from ordered concept list\n    # Earlier in list = higher activation\n    concept_activations = {}\n    for i, concept in enumerate(top_concepts):\n        # Decay activation based on position\n        activation = max(0.05, 0.95 - (i * 0.05))\n        concept_activations[concept] = activation\n\n    # Determine provider\n    if ollama_url:\n        provider = \"ollama\"\n    elif os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"):\n        provider = \"openai\"\n    elif os.environ.get(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"):\n        provider = \"anthropic\"\n    else:\n        provider = \"ollama\"  # Default to Ollama if available locally\n\n    mapper = CreativeMapper(provider=provider, model=model)\n    \n    # Override Ollama URL if specified (CreativeMapper uses localhost:11434 by default)\n    if ollama_url and provider == \"ollama\":\n        # Patch the URL into the mapper's client temporarily\n        import requests\n        original_post = requests.post\n        \n        def patched_post(url, json, timeout):\n            return original_post(f\"{ollama_url}/api/generate\", json=json, timeout=timeout)\n        \n        import types\n        requests.post = patched_post\n\n    try:\n        results = mapper.map_concepts_to_text(\n            concept_activations=concept_activations,\n            theme=theme,\n            mode=mode,\n            n_variations=1,\n            seed_moment=seed_moment,\n            user_constraints=user_constraints,\n        )\n        return results[0][\"text\"] if results else \"[No output]\"\n    except Exception as e:\n        return f\"[Generation error: {e}]\"\n    finally:\n        if ollama_url and provider == \"ollama\":\n            requests.post = original_post"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":61105,"output":1819,"cacheRead":12730,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75654,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774229617752}}
