{"type":"message","id":"ed778781","parentId":"dad60e1c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:35:52.445Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I also need to check the CreativeMapper's Ollama `_generate` method - it hardcodes `http://localhost:11434` but I want it to work with a custom URL. The issue is the CreativeMapper._generate hardcodes `http://localhost:11434/api/generate` for Ollama. Since I'm patching `requests.post` in demo.py, this should work - but let me verify the flow.\n\nActually, I realize my patching approach is wrong. In `demo.py`, I'm patching `requests.post` to always send to `{ollama_url}/api/generate`. But inside `CreativeMapper._generate()`, it calls `requests.post(\"http://localhost:11434/api/generate\", ...)`. My patch intercepts this and redirects to `ollama_url`.\n \nThe patch should handle this correctly since I'm reassigning `requests.post` to the patched version before instantiating the mapper, so all HTTP calls will route through my interception. I'm realizing the variable scoping here—`original_post` is assigned in the outer function scope before the try block, so even if an exception occurs during the requests import inside the try, the `finally` block will still be able to reference it and restore the original function.\n\nActually, there's a subtler issue: if `import requests` fails inside the try block and throws an exception, then `requests` never gets imported in that scope, so the `finally` block trying to access `requests.post` would fail with a NameError. The cleanest approach is to move the import to the top level of the module so it's always available, or use a context manager pattern to handle the patching more safely. requests` inside the try block. Let me move it outside.\n\nActually, looking at my generate_text function again:\n```python\nif ollama_url and provider == \"ollama\":\n    import requests\n    original_post = requests.post\n```\n\nIf `import requests` fails (rare, but possible in some environments), we'd get an exception here. But `import requests` is ALSO called inside `CreativeMapper._generate()` at the `elif provider == \"ollama\":` block, so if we're using Ollama, `requests` must be importable there too.\n\nThe real issue: if `import requests` fails in my generate_text, we never set `original_post`, and then in `finally: requests.post = original_post` we'd get NameError. Let me move the import outside the if block.\n\nI'll import requests at the top of the function to ensure it's always available, then handle the patching safely by checking if the original function exists before trying to restore it.","thinkingSignature":"befbf1d71aecae36c3fb5041991c8fd3626cf9dfaa59019aa33a91c0c1b364ce"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me fix the `generate_text` function to handle the requests patching more robustly:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v6ke73lpm9sw_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\demo.py","oldText":"    # Determine provider\n    if ollama_url:\n        provider = \"ollama\"\n    elif os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"):\n        provider = \"openai\"\n    elif os.environ.get(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"):\n        provider = \"anthropic\"\n    else:\n        provider = \"ollama\"  # Default to Ollama if available locally\n\n    mapper = CreativeMapper(provider=provider, model=model)\n    \n    # Override Ollama URL if specified (CreativeMapper uses localhost:11434 by default)\n    if ollama_url and provider == \"ollama\":\n        # Patch the URL into the mapper's client temporarily\n        import requests\n        original_post = requests.post\n        \n        def patched_post(url, json, timeout):\n            return original_post(f\"{ollama_url}/api/generate\", json=json, timeout=timeout)\n        \n        import types\n        requests.post = patched_post\n\n    try:\n        results = mapper.map_concepts_to_text(\n            concept_activations=concept_activations,\n            theme=theme,\n            mode=mode,\n            n_variations=1,\n            seed_moment=seed_moment,\n            user_constraints=user_constraints,\n        )\n        return results[0][\"text\"] if results else \"[No output]\"\n    except Exception as e:\n        return f\"[Generation error: {e}]\"\n    finally:\n        if ollama_url and provider == \"ollama\":\n            requests.post = original_post","new_string":"    # Determine provider\n    if ollama_url:\n        provider = \"ollama\"\n    elif os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"):\n        provider = \"openai\"\n    elif os.environ.get(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"):\n        provider = \"anthropic\"\n    else:\n        provider = \"ollama\"  # Default to Ollama if available locally\n\n    mapper = CreativeMapper(provider=provider, model=model)\n    \n    # Override Ollama URL if specified (CreativeMapper uses localhost:11434 by default)\n    import requests\n    original_post = None\n    if ollama_url and provider == \"ollama\":\n        original_post = requests.post\n        def patched_post(url, json, timeout):\n            return original_post(f\"{ollama_url}/api/generate\", json=json, timeout=timeout)\n        requests.post = patched_post\n\n    try:\n        results = mapper.map_concepts_to_text(\n            concept_activations=concept_activations,\n            theme=theme,\n            mode=mode,\n            n_variations=1,\n            seed_moment=seed_moment,\n            user_constraints=user_constraints,\n        )\n        return results[0][\"text\"] if results else \"[No output]\"\n    except Exception as e:\n        return f\"[Generation error: {e}]\"\n    finally:\n        if original_post is not None:\n            requests.post = original_post"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":68899,"output":1205,"cacheRead":12730,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82834,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774229728249}}
