{"type":"message","id":"66df9477","parentId":"d6fac497","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:38:12.838Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! The bug is in `sample_drift_path`. The `steps_per_tier + 1` - Python's `+` operator for list concatenation. Wait, no. `steps_per_tier` is an int, so `steps_per_tier + 1` would be fine. But `concepts` is... wait.\n\nLet me look at the code again:\n```python\nfor tier, concepts in [(high, steps_per_tier + 1), (mid, steps_per_tier + 1), (low, steps_per_tier)]:\n```\n\nWait, that's wrong! The loop is `for tier, concepts in ...` where the iterable is a list of tuples. \n\nOh! I see it now. I'm unpacking the tuple as `(high, steps_per_tier + 1)` where `high` is the actual list and `steps_per_tier + 1` is just an integer. So `concepts` gets bound to that integer instead of a list, which is why I can't call `len()` on it later.","thinkingSignature":"a37292298d676442dd568fbef769611049c17ccebceb2fd255f47cea4d705cc9"},{"type":"text","text":"Found the bug — I misstructured the loop in `sample_drift_path`. The tier assignment was wrong:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_570w21gq3z1l_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":78,"limit":30,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\llm_mapper.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":73797,"output":309,"cacheRead":12730,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86836,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774229881256}}
{"type":"message","id":"f04cfef2","parentId":"66df9477","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:38:12.851Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_570w21gq3z1l_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    \"\"\"\n    sorted_concepts = sorted(activations.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n    top = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[:30] if a > 0.1]\n    \n    if len(top) <= n_steps:\n        return top\n    \n    # Sample to get a spread across activation levels\n    high = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[:10] if a > 0.5]\n    mid = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[10:25] if a > 0.3]\n    low = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[25:] if a > 0.1]\n    \n    path = []\n    steps_per_tier = n_steps // 3\n    for tier, concepts in [(high, steps_per_tier + 1), (mid, steps_per_tier + 1), (low, steps_per_tier)]:\n        if concepts:\n            path.extend(random.sample(concepts, min(len(concepts), steps_per_tier + 1)))\n    \n    random.shuffle(path)\n    return path[:n_steps]\n\n\ndef build_tension_narrative(tensions: List[Tuple[str, str, float]]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Build a narrative description of the tensions at work.\"\"\"\n    if not tensions:\n        return \"\"\n    parts = []\n    for a, b, w in tensions[:3]:\n        parts.append(f\"the pull between {a} and {b}\")\n    return \"Through the piece, track: \" + \"; \".join(parts) + \".\"\n\n[255 more lines in file. Use offset=108 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774229892846}}
{"type":"message","id":"603b13cf","parentId":"f04cfef2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:38:22.172Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the bug now:\n```python\nfor tier, concepts in [(high, steps_per_tier + 1), (mid, steps_per_tier + 1), (low, steps_per_tier)]:\n```\n\nThis is unpacking the list `[(high, steps_per_tier + 1), (mid, steps_per_tier + 1), (low, steps_per_tier)]`. Each tuple is `(tier, concepts)`. So when we iterate:\n- First iteration: `tier = high`, `concepts = steps_per_tier + 1` (an INT!)\n\nThat's wrong. I meant to use a different data structure. Let me fix this to be clearer:\n\n\n```python\nfor concepts in [high, mid, low]:\n    k = min(len(concepts), steps_per_tier + 1)\n    if k > 0:\n        path.extend(random.sample(concepts, k))\n```\n\nThat's much cleaner — I just iterate through each tier directly and sample from it.","thinkingSignature":"bdb757a5ff00a0d2157a2613b53c781cf58d144edf4fc384146148c43e5f5748"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_psbkffhciik7_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\llm_mapper.py","oldText":"    path = []\n    steps_per_tier = n_steps // 3\n    for tier, concepts in [(high, steps_per_tier + 1), (mid, steps_per_tier + 1), (low, steps_per_tier)]:\n        if concepts:\n            path.extend(random.sample(concepts, min(len(concepts), steps_per_tier + 1)))\n    \n    random.shuffle(path)\n    return path[:n_steps]","new_string":"    path = []\n    steps_per_tier = n_steps // 3\n    for concepts in [high, mid, low]:\n        k = min(len(concepts), steps_per_tier + 1)\n        if k > 0 and concepts:\n            path.extend(random.sample(concepts, k))\n    \n    random.shuffle(path)\n    return path[:n_steps]"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74469,"output":442,"cacheRead":12730,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87641,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrit