{"type":"message","id":"ec8be100","parentId":"3e17571e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T01:38:35.572Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, there's also another issue. Looking at the code:\n\n```python\nhigh = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[:10] if a > 0.5]\nmid = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[10:25] if a > 0.3]\nlow = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[25:] if a > 0.1]\n```\n\n`sorted_concepts` is a list of tuples `(concept_name, activation)`. But `a` here is... wait, let me check: `sorted_concepts[:10]` would be 10 tuples. Each tuple is `(concept, activation)`. \n\nSo when I unpack with `c, a`, I get the concept string and its activation value, which works fine. But there's still something off with the logic.\n\nThe real problem is that even with valid activation thresholds like `a > 0.5`, when the steering is pure chaos (entropy = 1.0), all activations cluster around 0.5, so nothing actually exceeds the threshold and all the tiers end up empty. That's why the entropy reading of 0.999 is telling me the drift chamber is basically broken—not the sampler. The sampling code was throwing an error before I fixed it, but now that it handles empty lists properly, the drift chamber's dysfunction is the actual issue to debug. Rather than get stuck on that, I should focus on testing the LLM generation with Ollama and verifying the Paperspace URL works.","thinkingSignature":"73a8c30cf998a8ea962c0f379e1722aebaab494e7f64d8c539874d2313629edd"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me check the Ollama URL and test generation:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4acwn8knn73l_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\TOOLS.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74017,"output":360,"cacheRead":12730,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87107,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774229902188}}
